skills-ai-story.text: Your Hard-Won Skills. Over the past five weeks, you've learned what seniors know: codebase navigation, data flow tracing, integration patterns, and design-first thinking. These aren't just skills—they're superpowers.

AI's Raw Power. AI can generate code, explain concepts, refactor patterns, and write tests at incredible speed. But without context, it's just guessing. It doesn't know your codebase or your requirements.

You Provide Context. This is where you shine. You give AI the context it needs: codebase patterns, design constraints, edge cases, and integration requirements. Context transforms AI from guessing to executing.
AI Executes. With proper context, AI executes your vision at machine speed. Code generation, boilerplate, transformations—tasks that took hours now take minutes.
Senior-Level Output. The result? Senior-level productivity. Your knowledge plus AI's speed equals work that would take others days compressed into hours. You're not replaced—you're amplified!

workflow-story.text: Phase 1: You Design. Every great AI collaboration starts with you. Requirements, diagrams, edge cases—this is where your brain matters. AI can't know what the business needs. You do.
Phase 2: You Prompt. Break your design into clear, specific prompts. Include context from your codebase. Specify constraints and patterns to follow. A great prompt is half the work.
Phase 3: AI Executes. AI generates code based on your prompt. It's fast and often impressive. But here's the key: trust but verify. AI output is a first draft, not a final answer.
Phase 4: You Verify. This is critical. Does the code match your design? Does it handle your edge cases? Does it follow your codebase patterns? Your verification catches what AI misses.
Phase 5: You Integrate. Adapt AI output to your codebase style. Connect it to existing code. Add what AI missed. This integration step is where your codebase knowledge pays off.
Phase 6: You Test. AI often misses edge cases. Write tests yourself, or have AI generate them—but verify every assertion. Testing is where you ensure quality matches your standards.
Ship It!. You direct, AI executes, you verify. That's the loop. Master it, and you'll ship features faster than anyone thought possible while maintaining quality.

journey-complete-story.text: Week Zero: Where You Started. Six weeks ago, you wrote code for tickets. You debugged with print statements. You copied API examples. You coded first and thought later. Sound familiar?
You Learned Navigation. You can now read any codebase. Trace any call stack. Find any dependency. You're not lost in unfamiliar code anymore—you're at home.
You Learned Data Flow. You trace data flows systematically now. From user click to database and back. No more guessing where bugs come from—you find them methodically.
You Learned Integration. You integrate with resilience patterns. Timeouts, retries, circuit breakers. Your code doesn't just work—it handles failure gracefully.
You Learned Design. You design before coding now. Diagrams, edge cases, interfaces. When you open your IDE, you already know what you're building.
Week Six: Who You've Become. You're an engineer who owns features end-to-end, partners with AI, and executes at ten-x speed. The title will catch up to the skills. Keep going—you've earned this!

Course Complete!. You did it! You've gone from apprentice to someone who can design, code, and build real programs. The future is yours to create. Keep building, keep learning, keep thinking like an architect!
